ize=1> Khoal is supposed to be our raidmaster, but I haven't seen him online in quite some time. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Because of this, I am going to propose something for the guild.  <br>
<br>
<!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> How about a raid committee?</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :eek --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/eek.gif ALT=":eek"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
<br>
I have already spoken to Kligron about organizing a raid for the lower levels, possibly to Befallen.  He told me he would look into it, but I haven't heard anything back from him.<br>
<br>
Arich, would you like to help by organizing raids for that group of guildmates around your level?  If not, would you get someone in that group of you guys that have been fighting in Timorous to do that?  (Also get them to start using the message board.  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/smile.gif ALT=":)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> )<br>
<br>
Then, Khoal can still be in charge of raids for people 35+.  I don't want to take the position away from him, but I feel that we need some people who are very active players to do this.  Otherwise, our guild isn't much more than a chat room used in game.<br>
<br>
Also, I am going to schedule a guild meeting sometime in the near future, I believe. <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :D --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/happy.gif ALT=":D"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Do you all think that weekend evenings are best for that?  Please let me know.  There are many new faces in our Order, and not everyone knows eachother.  We need to get together so that we can hopefully learn about one another.  Another way to do this is to get everyone involved in using this board.  I feel that I have learned a lot more about people who use this board than those that don't, and I think it is a good place for guild business.<br>
<br>
Hope to see you all soon,<br>
Gira  <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :rollin --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/roll.gif ALT=":rollin"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugiradella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giradella</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10> at: 2/2/01 3:05:44 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/bbenevolentorder.showLocalUserPublicProfile?login=arichiena>Arichiena</A></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br>  Posts: 28<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/2/01 6:58:27 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic&index=1>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Raids</span><hr size=1>   I also feel that it would be too time consuming for a single person to be setting up raids for all the different levels and different time schedules. <br>
<br>
  The hardest part I have found is that people with the same approximate level aren't always free on the same day at the same time. <br>
<br>
  Would like to see 1 day of each month committed to a Raid/Dungeon run. The level and location of the raid can then be determined by the people available for it. Pick a day/time and start a list of who would commit to being there. The day/time of raid can be changed each month to accommadate different schedules. <br>
  <br>
  Would also like to see a second day of each month that would be dedicated for for helping guild members accomplish quests. If there is a quest that someone needs help in completing (None come to mind, Valamar) then maybe people would be willing to dedicate that one day to help. I feel that most people in our guild are more than willing to help others but I personally would find it easier if the day and time are set. I hate having to turn down requests for help because I have already committed to helping someone else.<br>
<br>
Just my 2cp worth <br>
Happy to help in anyway that I can<br>
     <br>
Arichiena <br>
