<br>
     First raid, Mistmoore, best turn out so far, actually had 2 groups.  About 30 minutes into it 2 groups became one...lasted awhile...didn't accomplish much because of trains etc.<br>
<br>
     Second raid, Permafrost, barely had one group.  A total of about 2 people responded to my raid post when it was up for over a week.  Every person was late (aka didn't think about the fact they were hanging out in Steamfont the night before).  By the time we got anywhere interesting raid was starting to split up.<br>
<br>
     Last raid, the anything in Velious raid, was announced in game over a few days and then posted here.  Total turn out: 3 people who were accidentally on when I was <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :( --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/frown.gif ALT=":("><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  <br>
<br>
On another note, I haven't had a SINGLE PERSON come to me and ask for a raid organized for anywhere.  Obviously Valmar needs a raid on Mistmoore, but we all know that you would have to pry his mouth open with a Fiery Avenger to get him to request anything from anyone else.  <br>
<br>
My point is:  Noone is gonna be successful in planning anything with no feedback from the guild.  If you don't wanna or can't go on the raid I plan then TELL ME WHERE YOU WANT/NEED TO GO AND I WILL PLAN IT.<br>
<br>
That's the story, and I'm sticking to it,<br>
Khoal<br>
Brother in need <br>
of a place to bleed <p></p><i>Edited by: <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ukhoal.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Khoal</A> at: 2/3/01 1:54:46 pm<br></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=#000044><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub11.ezboard.com/ugiradella.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Giradella</A>&nbsp; <IMG SRC=http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/black_thatch.gif BORDER=0 WIDTH=10 HEIGHT=10></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Jr. Administrator</span><br>  Posts: 83<br> <font color=#FFFFFF>(2/3/01 7:01:55 pm)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub11.ezboard.com/fbenevolentordergeneral.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=237.topic&index=3>Reply</a>   <BR><img src=http://eagle.cc.ukans.edu/~stinnett/Girasmall.jpg WIDTH=60 HEIGHT=60></td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title>   Re: Proposition for the guild</span><hr size=1> Khoal, I'm sorry about the poor turnout for the previous raids.  Maybe we should try to get another guild to go with us.  What do you think?  We seem to have a wide spread of levels in our guild, but not enough at each interval to make up effective raid groups.<br>
<br>
I agree that we need more feedback/participation.  Especially on this message board.  I'm going to make a hotkey that spams the guild to go to the message board.  I don't know how else to do it. <p><hr>
